  "wikitext": "\n'''1-1-140\n\nIrradiance (at a point of a surface)\n\nThe quotient of the radiant flux (dOe) incident on an element of the surface containing the point, by the area (dA) of that element.\n\nSymbol Ee\n\nUnit watt per square metre (W/m2)\n\n\nReference: C.I.E. (modified)\n\n\nNote: If the radiant flux Fe may be considered uniformly distributed over a finite plane surface of area A, the irradiance on this surface is given by ?? where Fe is the total radiant flux incident on the surface.\n\n{{IALAFooter}}\n\n{{languages|Irradiance}}\n[[Category:1.1 Basic Terms]]\n[[Category:Alphabetical Index]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 1970-89 Edition]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 2023 Revision]]"
